headline: Following historic power restoration effort in mountain region, Duke Energy announces more than $2.2 million committed to date for disaster relief, rebuilding and readiness in North Carolina
summary: Duke Energy and its Foundation today announced it has supported local communities across North Carolina with over $2.2 million in aid for disaster relief, rebuilding and readiness efforts since Hurricane Helene's impact. The announcement comes on the heels of the company's historic power restoration effort in the state's western mountain region.
